'''Level 0.41''', often referred to as '''Disease''', is a sublevel of [[Level 0]].

==Description ==
'''Level 0.41''', commonly referred to as '''Disease''', takes the appearance of the back rooms of a dated retail outlet, similarly to [[Level 0]]. However, '''Level 0.41''' seems to have been decaying for quite some time. The once yellow walls have been smudged and rotted into a dark, yellowish-green color. The wallpaper itself is chipped or peeled off of the wall, revealing the dark concrete walls underneath. The carpet has molded into a dark grey color, and is notably more moist, with sections peeled away similar to the wallpaper. The ceiling tiles are misaligned and shattered, wearing a light grey tint. The yellow fluorescent lighting that [[Level 0]] is known for has been replaced with a crimson hue. Most lights in the level flicker often, and many of the lights are completely broken. Certain lights within the level can be seen dangling from the ceiling, as if they were ripped out of place. {{Blurimage|file=0.41_Entrance.png|hovertext=rot.|caption=An entrance to Level 0.41 from [[Level 0]]. Note the instability and slightly green walls.}}While not in a literal sense, it seems that the level is attempting to keep itself alive. Rotten food can be found throughout the level, however, any resources within the level are entirely unusable. Alongside this, puddles of [[Object 12|Liquid Pain]] can be found in dented areas of carpet, which may pose a danger to anyone traversing the level. Certain areas of the level seem to have caved in under the weight of [[The Void]], leaving massive tears in the level's geometry. It is theorized that the areas that collapse under [[The Void]] are used to construct other levels, however this is unconfirmed. The deconstruction of the level, paired with the overall rot, makes breathing difficult. 

The entire level has a strange effect on it, seeming frozen in time. The lights are not given a chance to emit much of a buzz before they turn off, and no other sounds can be heard other than those made by the wanderer. Further contributing to the lack of ambience, the level lacks any form of life, with no deconstruction events being seen or heard. The level does not have the same [[Phenomenon 15|alone]] phenomena that [[Level 0]] has, nor does it have any of the hallucinatory events. Despite the clear corruption, the level is also linear, meaning that travelling in a straight line would act the same way as it does in [[The Frontrooms]]. 

== The Pause ==
A Pause is a rare phenomenon that may occur when wandering through '''Level 0.41'''. During this event, all motion, excluding that of the wanderer, ceases. This means that all flickering lights are frozen in their previous state, and any items dropped stay still in the air. Nothing can be moved during this period except for items in direct contact with a wanderer. Once an item is no longer in contact with a wanderer, it suddenly freezes and is unmovable until the event is over. Items inside things like bags or bottles are not affected by this until the container is dropped by the wanderer. In addition to the immobilization of objects, hunger and thirst cannot be alleviated during this period. This event is thought to be the cause of the lack of motion in the level's entities, possibly resulting in their current permanently paralyzed state.

== Entities ==
The level seems to have formerly had entities, however they are all seen paralyzed to this day from an unknown event. All recorded entities are [[Entity 8|Hounds]], [[Entity 3|Smilers]], [[Entity 5|Clumps]], and [[Entity 10|Skin-Stealers]]. 

==Outposts ==
Due to the nature of the level, creating a successful outpost is near impossible. 

==Entrances and Exits ==

=== Entrances ===
* Traversing extremely deep into [[Level 0]] may lead one here.
* Theoretically, an extremely unlucky noclip in [[Level 0]] may lead here.

=== Exits ===
* Noclipping is theoretically possible here, although the destination is unknown.
* The only other exits currently known are via the missing chunks of the level, which lead one to [[The Void]].

== Discovery ==
{{LoginColored|bg-color=#000000|text-color=#aaffaa|organization=M.E.G.|password=••••••••••••|body=Audio Log 1: I found it. After so long I've finally made it [[Level_0|here]], and it's just like they all say it is. Gonna keep this bad boy just in case I find something special, but until then I'm just gonna walk. Won't need to enter any other level, I know what I'm doing. I want to see how far I can go before I find something new. I want my name to be known.

Audio Log 2: All the lights just went out, kind of spooky. It doesn't look like there's any power in the entire level, but I guess I'll just keep moving. I think this means progress.

Audio Log 3: The lights are still out, and I'm pretty sure it's been days. Still haven't seen anything, but I did get a pile of almond water and cashews. Really needed those, I see why people don't normally willingly go here.

Audio Log 4: How far does this go? I've been walking for weeks now, I'm sure of it, and I've seen multiple doors. I've been so tempted to walk through them, but I need to make my name known. I don't care if it kills me.

Audio Log 5: Haven't used this thing in a while, I need to preserve battery. But I did find something. The wallpaper is sort of peeling, like it's rotting or something. It also feels a little bit more difficult to breathe over here, but it's probably nothing.

Audio Log 6: Holy shit. I found something. This is NOT the same level, I'm sure of it. The entire place, everything, is like...rotten? I'm not sure, but the lights are finally back on, and they're red. The walls are green, the carpet is grey, everything is just gross. Definitely not what I expected to see this far out, but it's something.

Audio Log 7: (out of breath) My heart is racing, I thought I was dead... I just saw something. It wasn't... it isn't moving, it's just standing there. Paralyzed. There isn't any food here, none that isn't rotten, so I might not make it much longer here. I'll at least be able to be known, I guess.

Audio Log 8: I found a tear. The entire corner is missing, it's just darkness below. I'm going to die here anyways, so I may as well risk it. I'm going to jump.

(The prior audio logs were found on a digital voice recorder in [[Level REDACTED]]. The name "Adam Thompson" was written on the recorder.)}}{{Collapse|initial='''Open Credits:'''|final='''Close Credits:'''|body=<br>
